Description: Tool for painting and retouching movie images
DescPort: <<
Film Gimp runs with shared memory disabled on Darwin. This is required because 
the
SysV shared memory implementation in the Darwin kernel is broken.
<<
DescDetail: <<
Film Gimp is a motion picture editing tool primarily used for painting and 
retouching of movie images. Its application in feature movie productions 
includes the movies Scooby-Doo, Harry Potter, Stuart Little and Stuart 
Little 2. Film Gimp is the most succ
essful open source tool in feature motion picture work today. Film Gimp is 
based on Gimp, the GNU Image Manipulation Program. Film Gimp is an independent 
project, separate from Gimp and GNU.
<<
